Brief description of what checks I chose to include in my smoke-test:
1. Check whether it can correctly copy input to output.
   (1) Correct exit code (0).
   (2) Correctly copy the content in the input.
2. Check if the implementation of --input is correct
   (1) Correct exit code (0).
   (2) Correctly copy the content in the input.
   ./lab --input=input.txt > result.txt
3. Check if the implementation of --output is correct
   (1) Correct exit code (0).
   (2) Correctly copy the content in the input to the output.
   ./lab --output=output.txt < input.txt
4. Check the handling of un-openable input file
   Correct exit code (2).
5. Check the handling of un-creatable output file
   Correct exit code (3).
6. Check the handling of non-existant input file
   Correct exit code (2).
7. Check the handling of invalid arguments
   Correct exit code (1).
8. Check the fault handling
   Correct implementation of --segfault and --catch, with exit code (4).
